name: Mindy Carter
blurb: “Let your outer glamour reflect your inner beauty.” A motto and personal quote I’ve lived by since I first discovered my ability to highlight the natural beauty we all possess. I remember as a toddler I would stare at my mom as she did her hair and makeup and thought, wow, I’m next. She’d kiss me on my cheek leaving me with this bright red lip print. When the coast was clear, I’d sneak into her vanity and give myself a makeover.  It’s funny just thinking back all those years but that’s when I fell in love with cosmetology. We all have innate talents that helps us establish an interest in what we are naturally good at; mine is beauty. As a professional I’ve worked for industry leaders such as Estee Launder, Nars, Napoleon Perdis and MAC Cosmetics. I’m a licensed cosmetologist and barber in the state of Utah and the owner of Mindy’s Make Overs. I look forward to meeting you and making you look your very best. See you soon.

name: Kimberly Warren
blurb:
Certified Lash Artist, located in Haltom City, TX. 76117

Now offering eyelash extension in my hometown- Texarkana one weekend per month. 
# 5 South Watlington Dr. 
Texarkana, TX. 75501


Semi-permanent eyelash extensions will give you longer, thicker and very natural looking eyelashes. They look so natural no one will know they are not yours! 

Extensions are perfect for everyday wear as well as special occasions. They are semi-permanent and made from synthetic fibers. Each lash is applied one by one to your own natural lashes. With proper care and touchup visits they can last a very long time. Normally a person's natural eyelash falls out every 60 - 90 days and a new lash grows in immediately. Therefore, it is necessary to get touch-ups to fill in the fallen lashes. About every 2 to 3 weeks is recommended, however, this will vary from person to person. Your natural lash cycle as well as how you take care of your lashes will affect how long they last. 

I look forward to working with each of you!
-Kimberly Warren

It's not just a glam party, it's also a chance for young girls to socialize, network and inquire about proper makeup application, skin and hair care.
   Tickets that are purchased are the deposit (non-refundable) for the package you select and to book your appointment. Upon arrival the remaining balance will be accepted at the door. (cash or credit/debit card payments only) It is imperative that you arrive on time for your appointment. A 5 - 10 minute grace period will be given to arrive after the appointed time. After 10 minutes you will forfeit your appointment and will not be allowed entrance into the glam party and all services are forfeited. 
   Before any services are performed we ask that each client arrive with a clean fresh face and washed dried hair. Before departing each girl will recieve a signature Simply Bei beauty bag to keep makeup and hair looking fresh and fabulous through out the night as well as digital behind the photos for memory and scrapebook purposes.

blurb:
Sonya became a Massage Therapist because of an injury. The hospital and doctors were unable to get to the root of the pain despite the needles, meds, and the many tests that they performed on her. It was her massage teacher who worked his magic and rid her of 80% of the pain. It was then that she discovered that she needed to be a part of that profession.  And now, 11 years later, her passion to help others with pain management has grown even stronger, so continuing education has become a great part of her life.

Not everyone experiences or handles pain in the same way, so a range of pressure and modalities such as: Neuromuscular Therapy, Myofascial Release, Hot & Cold Stone Therapy, and Stretching are used to customize your experience.

We Make A Difference One Muscle At A Time

Massage is energy work, and I am no stranger to sharing energy. 
Massage Is A Vehicle To Healing, So Let's Heal!

name: Angela Taylor
blurb:
Welcome to Anew You Studio. We are professional, industry experts in Advanced Permanent Cosmetics including 3-D eyebrow tattooing with single hair tattooing, eyeliner, lip color, scar camouflage, 3-D areola/nipple tattooing, and therapy to improve wrinkles and depressed scars. All of the work done at Anew You Studio is conducted with the use of multiple topical anesthetics for a truly pain free experience.

With an artist's eye for color, design and detail - our results are consistently superior. As believers of "less is more", we're conservative and always place our client's best interest first. Thoughtfully proceeding with caution, our experience brings the knowledge that more colorant can always be added - but once implanted it's there until if fades or is removed. Therefore, we strive to thoroughly understand client goals and create customized solutions. We are intentionally low volume so we never rush, taking time to do the job right.

We are committed to providing excellent work quality with the highest level of personal attention possible. We love topical anesthetics, use them liberally, and always go the extra mile to ensure a pain-free experience. As we strive to exceed expectations, we work hard to achieve your goals and hope that you are thrilled with our work.

Permanent color provides long lasting results that will be enjoyed every single day. Waking up with more confidence, feeling and looking your best - is as close as a phone call. Contact us at 503.409.8491 for more information or to schedule a free consultation.

blurb: A chemical expert transformed into a natural hair trailblazer, in 1998 Robin D. Before people were going green, natural silky, smooth hair was a specialty niche. The innovative technology of ionic blow dryers and ceramic tools began a natural hair care movement.

name: Gemini Wraps
blurb:
Cellulite and Fat reducing Body Wraps and Body Sculpting.  3 different style wraps to choose from.  Our wraps hydrate and nourish the skin.  They are not dehydrating and they don't have a strong smell.  The cloths we use are non latex and fragrance free.  Book your time online and we'll help you choose which wrap is most beneficial when you arrive.  

Ultrasound Cavitation and Radio Frequency RF can be booked independently or added to any Body Wrap Treatments. Penetrate cellulite and fat at a deeper level safely and in the specific areas you want to target.  Machine creates gentle vibration or frequencies (depending on service) that creates collagen reproduction.  No downtime or pain with services. 

Relax and enjoy while being pampered.  You don't work out, sweat it out, or weigh in here.  Same day and after hour appointments are available.  Receive discount or free treatments with referrals.  

Before you arrive:  
No perfumes or lotions.
Bring a bathing suit or extra underwear and bra or boxers for changing.
Drink lots of water.

A Facial/ Brow Bar is an innovative concept as a way to to offer quick spa services, while still delivering the feel of a full spa treatment to clients.
Nia Molina is located at Judith B, states “As a clinical esthetician my  mission is to improve skin health & care and make facials affordable for everyone."  A Facial Bar will allow her to deliver exceptional service and offer high quality products,  so clients can walk out of the salon with beautiful and rejuvenated skin.
Nia offers an extensive Facial Bar menu, including the SkinCeuticals Professional Peels, Derma Needling, Dermaplaning, High Frequency Therapy, Red & Blue Light Therapy and Facial Ultrasound Services
Aside from facials, Nia provides expert brow shaping along with brow & lash tinting. Packages available
Nia Molina can be found at Judith B, 261 N York St, Elmhurst, IL 60126

blurb: Hello Everyone, my name is Beth Cooper and it is my pleasure to introduce you to The Art Of Hair! For 12 years, I have dedicated my life to continuing education, specializing in color, precision hair cutting, and establishing a positive relationship with all of my guests. I grew up in the suburbs outside of Washington DC and have always had a knack for art and hair since the age of 4 years old. My career in the beauty industry started around 2003 in Boston, MA. There, I studied under very talented platform artists and soon moved back to Maryland where I took my own place behind the chair. Through very hard work, rigorous continuing education, and true passion, I now am considered a master stylist and color specialist. My goal is to give my guests a maintainable style suited to their lifestyle through a professional and comprehensive consultation.  I consider hair and art a way of life. It is not just a career for those of us who have the passion, but an outlet in expressing creativity.

In 2009 she began working as a Makeup Artist for the Smashbox Cosmetics line, where she remained until 2012. In 2012 she took the position as Makeup Artist/Color Specialist at Sephora until 2014. In 2014 Kiki obtained a position as Makeup Artist for the coveted Christian Dior Cosmetics Line, in this position she worked as a freelance artist until she was given the counter position at Nordstoms for the line. After one year in this position, she was given the "Beauty On Call" position for Nordstroms Oak Brook, the position she currently holds. 
Throughout these amazing positions Kiki has also maintained and grew her own personal brand "The Kiki~J Experience". Kiki~J has worked with agencies such as Ford, Factor, Galatea, and Wilhelmina (Modelogic Chicago)

waxingbyceleste.com

My Name is Celeste and I was born and raised in Brazil. I specialize in Brazilian waxing and body waxing. I provide multiple services that include waxing for both male and female, sugaring, facials, diamond tipped microdermabrasion, chemical peels, consultations, and skin care. I specialize in sugaring and Brazilian waxing and take pride in providing the best Brazilian wax in El Cajon, the East County, and all of San Diego. I am conveniently located in downtown El Cajon with easy access to the 8, 67, and 125 freeways.

I use 100% natural wax that includes 100% Organic Beeswax (hard wax), Eucalyptus Oil infused soft wax, and my very own 100% natural sugar wax (sugaring). I break traditional esthetic protocols by using a combination of all 3 100% natural types of wax. By taking advantage of the physical properties each wax has to offer, I am able to identify which wax is best suited for specific areas of the body. By doing this, I help minimize the pain felt by our clients. I simply do not limit ourselves with sticking with only one kind of wax!

My emphasis is not only on providing the best possible results with our skin treatments, but also informing and educating everyone who comes through our doors.  

Waxing and Skincare by Celeste

name: Camille Thompson
blurb: Beauty on Demand includes cut and style in all hair services. We order top quality hair for our clients but hair is not included in the base pricing. Maintenance is included in fusions and micro links but not for sew ins or bonding. Sew in extensions are guaranteed for the first 3 weeks after installation. After which, a cost will be incurred to repair or tighten. Beauty on Demand does not offer chemical processing of the hair of any kind. If necessary, coloring or perming must be done before the scheduled appointment. New clients may be asked for a deposit to lock in appointments due to frequent cancellations. That deposit will be included in total visit cost. Beauty on Demand is open for early bird or late night appointments to fit any busy schedule. We are mobile and will travel to your location for your convenience. Call or text for immediate response. 214-364-3224

name: Bonda
blurb:
When I was 14 years old, my mom sent me to the hair salon. I watched the stylist do my hair. When she finished,  I said to myself, "I can do that!!" I went home, took my hair apart, redid it, and I've been doing hair since.  With the exception of a few years here and there, I've been working diligently for over 20 years to perfect my craft. While I pride myself on being versatile, my skilled specialities are short hair, promoting healthy hair, edgy cuts,  and adding extensions. I've worked hard to establish a top notch reputation within my industry. Being MBE, DBE, and SBR certified has afforded me the opportunity to establish that same reputation with goverment agencies by providing contractual services to a military base and in a juvenile detention center.
I continously thank the Lord above for my gift. In return, I will continue to provide the best customer service that I can while uplifting and encouraging those that sit in my chair.  I hope you enjoy what you see and look forward to hearing from you soon!

I believe in constantly keeping up with continuing education, because no matter how seasoned a stylist you may be you can always learn something new. blurb: Sara Ashley Hurchik has joined the Salon Forza team as a hairstylist, makeup artist, eyelash extension specialist and nail technician. She attended Marymount Manhattan College in uptown NYC with Business and Performing Arts majors and continued on to pursue her dream of becoming a hairstylist. She graduated from Lowell Academy, recieving her licensure in Cosmetology and Nail Technology. She is currently certified in SoCap Hair Extensions, Coppola Keratin Smoothing System, Elizabeth Grady Advanced Makeup Artistry, Facial & Body Waxing, Shellac and Axxium Gel Polish, and more. Sara believes strongly in continuing education to learn cutting edge styles and trends. She has won numerous awards for her formal and avant garde upstyling and makeup artistry. I'm at one of the best salons in Columbia, Image Makers Salon. It's a beautiful salon with an amazing support system. We have our own booking system so please call the salon at 803-736-3614 to schedule your appointment! I look forward to pampering you!

My mother is a well known hair artist and I grew up watching her in awe. She has motivated me and pushed me towards success and I am thankful for her. I have participated in a number of hair competitions and hair shows. I have won first place in a hair/fashion battle the year of 2014, and second place in a hair cut and color competition based in LA the year of 2015. Many more to come. Also I have participated in Editorial shoots, fashion shows, and my work is also featured in the magazines such as Black Passion, Salon Source, and Sophisticates' Hair. 

I truly love what I do, not for the money, but for the experience and the joy of making someone feel better and enhancing the beauty within themselves. 

So now that you know a little about me, let me get to know you. Book an appointment to experience the Tymeless Beauty in you.

See you soon,

MarQui

name: Kiki Evans
blurb:
Kiki’s passion for doing hair sparked in The City of Brotherly Love. She was inspired by the broad spectrums of fashion and personal styles in Philadelphia. Graduating from the distinguished Jean Madeline Aveda Institute, Kiki already had over 5 years assisting experience, one of the salons being the first organically based salon in Philadelphia, Juju Salon & Organics.

Being in the world of organic beauty, Kiki took as many educational classes and workshops as possible. She became well-versed in over fourteen organic product and color lines, discovering her deep rooted passion and dedication to executing her skills with quality organic products. Wanting to further her career, she leapt at the chance to open a new organic salon with four of her fellow stylists. Helping build a new salon from the ground up was a challenge Kiki embraced, and being part of the Lunarosa Salon family allowed her to grow significantly as a stylist, sharing her light and love for the industry and mother earth.

Having fallen in love with San Francisco while visiting a friend, and craving growth in a place that would offer her new experiences, Kiki packed up her car and drove across country. Her ten year journey was to be continued in the bay area. Kiki’s work is very much about tailoring her skills to suit her clients personal aesthetic, while celebrating self love, self care and self expression… and what better place to do that than in San Francisco!

name: Kimberly Armstrong
blurb:
My name is Kimberly Armstrong, and I’ve been designing natural-looking Permanent Makeup since 2004. I’ve completed thousands of procedures at many of the well-known spas throughout Southern California, including Spa Gregorie’s and Salon Sauvage, and in 2014 I opened up my own facility in Laguna Hills called Beauty Hideaway (www.beautyhideaway.info) where we do Permanent Makeup, traditional makeup classes and lash extensions.

Before I got into Permanent Makeup, I was a professional makeup artist and worked “on location” for Lancôme and Clinique – this helped me develop a knack for the most difficult part of the process: the design. I later trained at the prestigious International Institute of Permanent Cosmetics and became certified in Micropigmentation. But my passion for being the best in the industry, despite the fact that the state of California does not regulate the tattooing industry, drives me to continue regularly training with a variety of schools and educators so that I can always deliver the most advanced techniques available, provide the absolute best products on the market and stay on top of all OSHA guidelines for health safety.

If you’d like more information, feel free to visit my Website (www.kimberlyarmstrong.com) where you’ll find links to an overview video with lots of information, my Yelp page with testimonials and photos, as well as Facebook and Twitter. If Permanent Makeup feels like a good fit for you, I look forward to meeting you soon!

name: Styles
blurb:
APPOINTMENTS - APPOINTMENTS  New customers must have a card on file. You have the option to pay cash once you come in. 
CONFIRMATION - You get 2 confirmations, one 2 days before your appointment and one the day before your appointment. You have 2 hours to confirm your appointment. Failure to confirm your appointment will open your slot and you will need to reschedule.
NO KIDS - NO kids allowed, unless being serviced.
BEING LATE -  If you are 10 minutes late, then there is a $15 late fee. If you are 20 minutes late, then there is a $25 late fee. If you are 30 minutes late, then you are considered a walk-in and your service is regular price (if your appointment was scheduled for the special).
LATE CANCELLATIONS - You do not get a special for future appointments. In order to qualify for the special again, you have to come 3 consecutive appointments without being late or canceling.
NO CALL NO SHOWS - No Call No Shows result in not getting a special. For future appointments, you have to leave a $25 security deposit that will not go toward your service, it will be to secure your appointment. In order to be eligible for a special, you will need to make a ONE time payment of $100 that will be added to your service (which will be effective immediately).
 WALK-INS -  Do not qualify for the special, appointments only!

Having been born and raised in Southern California with a lifelong educational background in fine art, it inevitably brought him to Los Angeles where he quickly started building a name for himself in the underground art scene. His undeniable edge and flare for the avant-garde quickly led to collaborating with LA's top fashion designers landing him spreads in fashion magazines and keying hair for runway shows. From there, it wasn't too long before his extensive fashion portfolio launched his creative skills to the world of celebrity, music, and entertainment.

Jeremy currently divides his time traveling between LA, SF, and NYC, providing housecall services to the rich and famous, working on set of music videos and fashion shoots, styling celebrities for the red carpet, and inspiring as well as educating other artists in and out of seminars.

blurb: Hi there, I'm Juliana. My vision is to empower women by improving their image. Until i became of age and I understood that going to my hairstylist made me feel good. My experience was the ability to capture the essence of my femininity.  I loved that my stylist always understood my hair needs, as well as on a personal level, she was like a friend.  It felt like I was in a calm, warm and safe environment. This ignited my passion for being a hairstylist. Hairstyling has given me the ability to interface with so many people, and making them feel good is the most gratifying feeling a career can give. My twelve year journey has allowed me to opportunity to spread my passion and joy into individuals lives.

name: Lori Fagan
blurb: Lori Fagan is a graduate of Morgan State University with a B.S. Degree in Telecommunication as well as Loyola University with a M.Ed in Early Childhood Education. She received her Certified Professional Coaching (CPC) Certificate from the Fowler International Academy of Professional Coaching. She is also a sisterlocks and eyelash consultant. She founded Black Butterfly Recovery Coaching only after being diagnosed with stage one breast cancer at the age of 43. She discovered they were limited or little to no services available to young working women with breast cancer. She also noticed that the lack of resources negatively impacted women under the age of 50, diagnosed with breast cancer seeking support in recovering and surviving with breast cancer. The sole purpose of Black Butterfly Recovery Coaching is to "help young women with breast cancer live a life of wellness and live the abundant life God desires for them to have." Lori began her journey as a sisterlocks and eyelash consultant after receiving one full year of chemotherapy and much to her surprise during her treatment she discovered her sisterlocks continued to grow and strive. But unfortunately, her eyelashes fell out. She decided she wanted to help other women maintain their beauty while receiving chemotherapy and to not lose their hair or eyelashes by installing sisterlocks and lavish lashes. She has the power to create transformational masterpieces!

The body wants to heal itself as we all have that self healing mechanism. I do this in one of four ways: wellness coaching, mindfulness meditation, massage therapy and/or Reiki Energy Healing 

Visit me on my Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/joettapg

name: Lisa Cort
blurb: I am a mommy of one 11 year old boy and wife to my wonderful husband of 8 years.  I have also been a surrogate mother to 6 babies over the last 9 years.  I spent that time trying to figure out what I wanted to do.  Banking, Bartending.... it was great but it wasn't satisfying.  I was looking for that special something that I could do all day and go home feeling accomplished.  My passion to do lash extensions came from me loving having my own lash extensions.  I felt beautiful and confident having them on.  It's hard to believe that LASHES have that effect but they truly do!  I became an Esthetician in 2010 and quickly decided that Lashes was going to be my niche. I attended a training in May of 2010 for Xtreme Lashes.  I passed my certification with Xtreme Lashes in November of 2011. Since then I opened up a lash studio in my very own home in Murrieta.  It's my little piece of heaven. blurb:
A little bitty bit about me . . . .

I am a Sonoma county born and bread girl in love with her career choice. After high school I spent time in college as well as dabbling in many other career ventures, all of which I was good at. The only problem? I wasn't passionate about them like I was about the beauty industry. Being behind the chair I am able to connect with incredible people, help them with confidence and empowerment as well as make them feel beautiful(handsome)as the individual and special women(men) that they are.

Eight years later I am still so incredibly passionate and in love with being a stylist and can't even imagine my life doing anything else. My specialties lie within color as well as bridal hair/makeup and extensions. Creating the perfect look for my ?clients as well as reinventing their approach to hair are also something I do very well. I believe that hair is not only an outward expression of ones individuality but also an opportunity to highlight the most unique and intricate features each person possesses.

Thank you so very much for the opportunity to work with each and everyone of you. I look forward to every appointment!!!

XOXO,

Cari Anne Crachiola

blurb:
Hollywood Hair Clinics is a private salon that was diligently created for those seeking a nontraditional salon experience.  We are committed to those affected by the devastation of hair loss due to illness and / or medications.  Based on our research and the increasing cases in America for Men, Women and Children, we recognize at Hollywood Hair Clinics that we must not only provide a safe private location in which our clients may come and feel comfortable, knowing that their needs will be met.  But rather acknowledging that we will also provide them with all the necessary resources they will need to maintain their flawless look once they leave our facility.

Our goal is to restore, rebuild, encourage, love, educate and CHANGE!  Change the way they look.  Change the way they accept their condition.  Change their outlook.  Change what was once the impossible.  Simply CHANGE!  
Hollywood Hair Clinics is a Hair Salon offering services coast to coast,  originating in the Kansas City, MO area with exceptional services to exceed the most demanding standards!

name: Donald Cooper
blurb: Margaret’s is a second generation hair salon. The original owner Margaret Cooper held her grand opening in the spring of 1962. Over the last 40 plus years her commitment to excellence was top priority.  In 1986 a new leader emerged keeping in step with the newest trends. Donald Cooper was appointed to guide the salon into the 21st century. Having been raised in the salon environment he knew the mission statement. Traveling the country and attending the latest hair shows he would bring the latest trends and techniques back to the community. Specializing in all types of hair textures, whether your hair is; wavy, straight, curly or natural we meet the needs of our clients. Our business is based on the belief that our clients needs are of the utmost importance. The entire team is committed to meeting those needs. As a result, a high percentage of our business is from repeat customers and referrals. We welcome the opportunity to earn your trust and provide you with the utmost professional service.

name: Camilla Johanson
blurb: My name is Camilla and I love doing hair! I found a passion for hair as a teenager. It started when my older sister's friend asked me to do an updo for a dance, and to be honest, I didn't really even know how to do an updo. But I did it anyways and guess what!?!? The updo was amazing! After that dance, I had tons of girls wanting their hair done by me for dances. That was when I knew I needed to go to beauty school. After high school, I went straight to Paul Mitchell in Provo, UT. I received 2000 hours of learning on how to cut, color and style hair. I also was able to be taught by some of the most amazing professionals in the business. After school, I got married and moved to Las Vegas, where I have done hair for over 6 years. I have worked with every hair type, 3 years of it on exclusively male haircuts. I have also been featured on the TV series My Big Fat American Gyspy Wedding, where I did an updo for a wedding. I am now onto my new adventure in hair, renting a station, to be able to truly enjoy the clients I have!!! I love hair and I love making people happy, it is the best part of my day!

name: Sara Rashidi
blurb:
If thinking about trying a new stylist gives you anxiety, you should just take a chill pill and come see me. There is nothing uptight or judgmental about me. I will be honest with you about your hair, and if you dont know what u want, I'll give you some ideas you'll most likely love. My first concern is your hair's health. Where is it damaged? What habits have contributed to its damage? Is it repairable? I push for starting a new look with a clean slate. Removing or repairing the damage as needed, education about how to maintain its health, and an inspirational lecture on respecting oneself and one's hair. Humorous anecdotes free of charge. Sarcasm extra.
I'll break the ice, I'll open you up to new ideas, I'll listen to your boyfriend problems, I'll make you famous, and I'll charge you only what I could see myself paying for the same service. Its a journey for the both of us, and you'll leave feeling awesome.

name: Stephanie Betts

From selling beauty supplies to going to cosmetology school. Since that lifechanging decision I've been thriving. I attend every education opportunity I can; Vidal Sassoon, Tigi Academy, Bumble and Bumble University, L'Oreal Professionel, Redken and Kerastase to name a few. It is my personal goal to keep thriving and putting my extensive education to good use. I'd absolutely love the opportunity to give you amazing hair!

blurb:
Welcome! I'm Darlene Hardoon

My goal is to take your nails and make them look and feel the way you've always pictured them using products that I select specifically for clients with allergies and other chemical sensitivities, as well as ethically produced products made in the USA, vegan, at least three free, and cruelty free.

My place is unisex, free of judgement, and respectful of your time.

My goal is to also have products that will last you and look natural enough to fool even professionals, even if you are hard on your hands, are a nail biter, or have been disappointed by salon visits in the past.

I'm a Floridian, former nailbiter, volunteer therapy dog team tester with two kids and a German Shepherd Dog that grew tired of cheap salons hurting me when I was going there for help. I talk straight and am gently honest, and believe that you deserve better than where you get your services done now. I want you to look better and better as time goes on, and to have strong, healthy nails that you will be proud of. So come book with me :-)

name: AnMarie Smock
blurb: My name is AnMarie Smock and I am a licensed cosmetologist and going back to school to become an esthitician as well. I didn't always know I wanted to be in this field but I have always enjoyed it. I perused my passion for hair and beauty and fell in love with Tricoci University and their staff at the Peoria campus. The program is 11 months long and I graduated in 10 months. Through all of the perms, updos and cuts I knew I was in the right place. I love all of the detail and precision that go into every single cut and color. There is always new techniques and styles coming around and I love all the knowledge this career offers. I feel more at ease with a pair of shears or coloring brush in my hands.  Everyday is a new adventure and new techniques to learn. I really enjoy cutting hair, coloring, perming and doing roller sets. I seem to go to my own happy place when I cut hair. My favorite is styling hair to emphasize the guests' natural beauty. I can't wait to see what this career teaches and has in store for me.

blurb: Im a motivated stylist that loves to create the perfect look for each individule client. Always willing to learn knew techniques to create new looks. As a young girl my family saw the passion i had for doing hair. They have pushed me to do things that i didnt know i could do myself and they are my biggest fans. I started doing family, classmates, family friends, and my moms coworkers hair. When i was able to buy my little brother school supplies and christmas gifts, thats when i knew this was the real deal. When i was in high school i worked as a shampoo assistant every day after school and on the weekends. That experience taught me a lot of the basics of the business. But going to cosmetology school made me a business women and well rounded as a stylist. I love this industry and all the things it has to offer. My career is my soulmate.

name: Sara McRae
blurb:
I provide therapeutic massage and Touch For Health balances at Zenbrio House in Eugene, Oregon. 

If you wish to bill insurance, please see my website for information that is required before you book your appointment: www.sjmcrae.massagetherapy.com

My massage style is a good fit if you seek specific treatment to improve compromised areas, and want to enjoy relaxation and overall balancing of the body at the same time. I specialize in Deep Tissue, Swedish, Acupressure, and hydrating tissue to reduce pain. 

My holistic balance is a good fit if you want to balance your posture, and improve physical comfort and reduce stress in your life. I specialize in Touch for Health (TFH) applied energy kinesiology, a system of balancing one’s body and energy to align with goals and promote optimum health and vitality! 

What are the benefits of Touch for Health?
* Helps to achieve life goals
 * Increases energy and mood
 * Improves posture and structural balance
 * Relieve stress, anxiety, pain and discomfort

I am also a certified Touch For Health Instructor, passionate about sharing the powerful and simple techniques of TFH to empower people to improve their own health, and the health of those around them.

I believe healing is not the fixing of something broken, it is the integration of the parts back into the whole. No matter where you are in life's journey, there is always more to discover about yourself.

Oregon License 12674.

Thank you for your continued support and for the confidence that you have placed in me.  And for following me through out the years, and helping me celebrate the opening of Beauty By Bridget in The Salons at Stone Hill.
I would like to assure you that I do not take this confidence for granted.
At Beauty By Bridget, I work with a purpose – to provide best-in-class service to my customers, which I also consider my friends.
My philosophy has always centered on the belief that customers should be
treated in a fair and balanced manner. This belief, and the passion I have for this industry started 15 years ago when i did my first haircut.
You have my assurance I am committed to ensuring that Fair Dealing, your beauty needs, and putting a smile on your face when you leave the salon is central to everything I do, and its a belief I stand by with my valued clients.
Again, thank you all for all the encouragement, your commitment, and the client-friend relationships we have built.  I am very grateful.
Yours sincerely,
Bridget

name: Kai Lopes-Stovell
blurb:
MY BEAUTY STORY
Born and raised in the Boston area, I initially prepared for a career in medicine at Atlanta’s prestigious Spelman College. Amidst the hustle and bustle of pre-med life, I transformed my love for styling my own hair into a steady business of doing blow-dries for fellow students right out of my dorm room.

Ten years later, I am thankful to have mastered a wide range of skills, from colors and cuts, to relaxers, dreadlocks and natural styles, to weaves and extensions. My approach to the craft remains simple: hairstyle is a means of self-expression, culture, personal style and the times. I believe that preparation and versatility of style should never compromise the overall health of the hair and scalp. I pride myself on establishing a deep, personal connection with each of my clients. 

Although I dream of one day owning my own salon and applying my styling skills to the coiffures of illustrious celebrities, I look forward to welcoming clients to enjoy the Kai experience. Once you enter this realm, there is no turning back!

name: Marie LaBreche
blurb:
Marie is an Independent Cosmetologist offering services for women, men and children ranging from hair to nails. 


Description

Marie LaBreche has always had an eye for beauty and has been professionally sharing her talents with clients since she became a cosmetologist in 2007. In the beginning of her career, Marie offered her services at a full service salon in the Metro Area. She proudly built her business while focusing on continuing education in cutting, razor cutting, perming, and coloring to ensure that her clients were always receiving the highest quality of services and were offered access to cutting edge techniques and products. 

 As Marie continued to expand her field of expertise to facial waxing, and natural nail manicures, including gel polish, she moved onto a spa where she could offer a more robust offering of services to her clients. She later earned her Manager's License and is now an independent contractor in a busy suburban salon, Suite Haven in Blaine, MN. Marie proudly focuses her talents on families and achieving amazing results at a reasonable price. In addition she also earned her Educator License during this time and substitute teaches at Empire Beauty School ranging from pre salon theory, to advanced techniques, to board and licensure testing. 

Marie has been a Director on the Board with the Salon Spa Professional Association since 2016 after being a long time member. MNSSPA provides education for life-long learning, lobbying, and supporting the Cancer Wig Foundation to improve the lives of the beauty industry professional.

name: Tega Ainslie
blurb: I have had an amazing career working as a stylist and hair artist since 2006 and I love every minute of it! I could not have found a more perfect profession for myself, I love that I get to express my creativity everyday and I actually get paid for it! My love for the art and beauty in hair design lead me to enroll in the Cosmetology program at Salt Lake Community College, Utah in 2004. Upon completion in early 2006, I went to work at Regis Salon in West Valley City, Utah. Not long after starting my career with Regis, I became the salon manager and lead a great team of stylists. After three great years, I then went to work at the Regis Salon in Sandy. Six months later, I moved to the beautiful Black Tie Salon and Day Spa in Murray as a Master Stylist. I now own a studio setting salon called "Hair Design by Tega". Throughout my career, I have focused on continued education by attending many advanced training workshops, classes, shows, and became certified in different hair extension techniques and the Brazilian Blowout. I specialize in hair color, cutting, bridal and wedding hairstyles, and have received a lot of experience working on different textures of hair. I keep up on the industries latest trends, techniques, and technology. I have the best clientele in the world, I would not be where I am today without them!

name: Darren Roca
blurb: During my service in the military I discovered a passion for hair cutting.  It started out as a hobby, while cutting my own hair and grew into a desire to learn more about the art of clipper and shear cutting.  I had overwhelming support from co-workers and friends.  In 2006 I decided to enroll in barber school in Newport News, VA.  My active duty commitment made it difficult to fully commit, so I placed it on hold.  I was honorably discharged from the Navy in 2009. The opportunity to follow my dream presented itself and I moved to Chicago. I completed barber school and became a licensed barber after 4 years of cutting hair.  Hard work and dedication landed me a chair at the prestigious Hyde Park Hair Salon where I honed my skills and built real in-the-field experience for the next 9 months. An opportunity presented itself for me to open my own shop, as I've always had a vision for a different type of barbershop where my clients can come in expecting a service and leave with an experience. Urbane Blades is the result of the journey. Book your appointment today!

name: David  Swerddling
blurb: I am a master cosmetologist and the proud owner of my own studio, Salon David at Salon Studios Perimeter. Hair has been my life long passion. I have been specializing in corrective color for 30 years  and I strive to make each and every one of my clients that walks out of my studio door leaves %100 satisfied because I understand that your hair is a walking canvas for the world to see, and seeing my clients happy is why I do what I do and do the best color in town

name: alyssa coyle
blurb: Alyssa started her career in 2009 when she enrolled in beauty school. She began working right out of school for 4 years in a salon in St. Cloud, when she eventually made her way back to her hometown in Elk River. She is truly passionate about her career,she loves staying up on the latest fashion trends.Being able to use her creativity and being able to produce a beautiful new look for her clients is what she lives for! She is trained to do all services but she is truly passionate with hair extensions, up-dos as well as hair coloring. She specializes in 3 types of hair extensions you can learn about when you set up a consultation

name: Jessica Baker
blurb: Hey There!!! I'm a natural nail specialist so therefore I do not apply artificial nails!! I enjoy maintaining the health and natural appearance of your own nails! Yes I can Glam them up Too!!  I enjoy being in the beauty industry and making you feel Glamorous!! I also make all natural sugar scrubs that I incorporate in my services which leave you feeling soft and hydrated!! I also specialize in working with diabetic clients!! You don't want to miss out! I promise you won't be disappointed!!
